(default 100), generating fresh random values for the with-clause
params on each iteration via the runtime arbitrary[T] helpers.

Per-block output:
  <desc>: 100 iter, OK
  <desc>: counterexample at iter <N>: p=<v>, q=<v>, ...

Followed by a 'P/T checks passed' summary; exit 1 if any block
recorded a counterexample.

check v1 (issue #44): supported with-clause types are Int, Bool,
Char, String, and lists of those primitives. Other types raise a
panic at runtime. Shrinking is deferred to v1.x; protocol-based
